title: For Sale:  USN G1 Flight Jacket
postcontent: I recently bought a few things from a family friends estate including a G1 flight jacket (been the standard USN/USCG/USMC aviator issue forever and in service since 1930 or so). He had been in the service since he was 17 in WWII (had the underage vet pins too) and was a career navy guy with 40 some years in. I have always wanted one of these, but unfortunately it is too short! I am 6'2", 250lbs, and this fits perfectly except for the length. As you can see in the pics, it is 26" long from shoulder to waist, and I need a 27" jacket at least. I wear XL in my motorcycle leather jackets, and a size 46-48 suit coat, so this is pretty spot on with its XL size tag. I am unsure as to the age of it as the family said he had had many of these over the years, but the shorter length lends to it being a bit older (not an exact dating method obviously).Jacket has a few spots on it from use, but nothing terrible, and has that older leather smell, but hey, its actual goatskin, so it should! The only real issue I can see is the gentleman removed the pocket buttons (for whatever reason), and one pocket flap is a bit wrinkled from storage, but it should be able to be ironed/pressed out pretty easily.Actual military issued jackets don't come up for sale as often, and this one has never had any patches put on it (which was a plus to me as I am not a naval aviator), and I am just looking to get back what I paid so I can put the funds towards one that will fit. I will also trade for a longer one in similar condition on the off chance someone has the opposite problem (a 2xl or size 48-50 would fit the bill I think).
